cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.RO, cs.AI 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on investigating ground-aerial uplink non-orthogonal multiple access (NOMA) cellular networks, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper proposes a joint optimization problem to minimize the UAV mission completion time by optimizing the UAV trajectory and UAV-GBS association order, which involves information theory concepts such as channel coding and modulation. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper formulates a mixed integer non-convex problem and involves infinite variables, which requires system and control theory techniques to tackle the problem. 
4. cs.RO (Robotics) - The paper involves the use of a rotary-wing unmanned aerial vehicle (UAV) and proposes an efficient solution with predefined hovering locations, which falls under the domain of robotics. 
5. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes an iterative UAV trajectory design by applying successive convex approximation (SCA) technique, which is a machine learning technique and falls under the domain of artificial intelligence.
